<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 01:03:03 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>个人导航能力的决定因素</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/determinants-of-individual-navigation-ability</link><description>人们的导航能力存在很大差异，这是由多种因素决定的。在这篇综述中，Yavuz 和 Spiers 将这些因素整理为寿命、生活方式和个人属性，并讨论了它们对导航影响的认知和神经机制。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/determinants-of-individual-navigation-ability.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 01:02:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/determinants-of-individual-navigation-ability</guid></item><item><title>放射诱导的淋巴细胞减少症的治疗前风险模型与不可切除的 III 期 NSCLC 患者的辅助 durvalumab 疗效相关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pretreatment-risk-model-for-radiation-induced-lymphopenia-is-associated-with-adjuvant-durvalumab-efficacy-in-patients-with-unresectable-stage-iii-nsclc</link><description>我们能否通过预测严重的放射诱导淋巴细胞减少症 (RIL) 来预测免疫治疗的成功？治疗前 NSCLC 列线图显示，只有低 RIL 风险的患者才能从辅助 durvalumab 中获益，从而有可能实现个性化 RIL 缓解和优化免疫治疗。请在 RedJournal 中阅读。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pretreatment-risk-model-for-radiation-induced-lymphopenia-is-associated-with-adjuvant-durvalumab-efficacy-in-patients-with-unresectable-stage-iii-nsclc2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:47:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pretreatment-risk-model-for-radiation-induced-lymphopenia-is-associated-with-adjuvant-durvalumab-efficacy-in-patients-with-unresectable-stage-iii-nsclc</guid></item><item><title>微管蛋白可防止有毒蛋白质团块的形成</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/tubulin-prevents-toxic-protein-clump-formation</link><description>“这让我们产生了以下想法：如果我们不是阻止液滴的形成，而是创造条件来驱动液滴内的 Tau 和 α 突触核蛋白朝着健康的方向发展，阻止它们走上疾病的道路，会怎么样呢？”该作品的共同通讯作者说。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/tubulin-prevents-toxic-protein-clump-formation2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:32:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/tubulin-prevents-toxic-protein-clump-formation</guid></item><item><title>利用人工智能代理促进公共物品博弈合作</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/promoting-cooperation-in-the-public-goods-game-using-artificial-intelligent-agents</link><description>Hintze, A., Adami, C. 利用人工智能促进公共物品博弈合作&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/promoting-cooperation-in-the-public-goods-game-using-artificial-intelligent-agents2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:17:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/promoting-cooperation-in-the-public-goods-game-using-artificial-intelligent-agents</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现了可以复活耗尽的抗癌 T 细胞的开关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-discover-the-switch-that-revives-exhausted-cancer-fighting-t-cells</link><description>科学家们发现了新的遗传规则，这些规则决定了免疫系统的“杀手”T细胞是否仍然是强大的长期防御者，或者是否会变得疲惫不堪和失效。通过构建 CD8 T 细胞状态的详细遗传图谱，研究人员确定了推动这些细胞恢复弹性或衰竭的关键分子开关。值得注意的是，仅禁用两个以前未知的基因即可恢复耗尽的 T 细胞的肿瘤杀伤能力，同时保留其提供持久免疫保护的能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-discover-the-switch-that-revives-exhausted-cancer-fighting-t-cells.webp" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:02:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-discover-the-switch-that-revives-exhausted-cancer-fighting-t-cells</guid></item><item><title>人工智能如何解开海洋生物的深海秘密</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-ai-could-unlock-deep-sea-secrets-of-marine-life</link><description>珊瑚礁是数十种物种的家园和觅食地，这些物种依赖它，就像林地生物依赖树木一样。它经历了冰河时代，但它是否能承受工业捕捞、深海采矿和气候变化带来的日益增加的压力，部分取决于数据。如果我们不知道它的存在，我们如何保护它？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-ai-could-unlock-deep-sea-secrets-of-marine-life2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 23:47:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-ai-could-unlock-deep-sea-secrets-of-marine-life</guid></item><item><title>初创公司正在建设第一个使用人脑细胞的数据中心</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/start-up-is-building-the-first-data-centre-to-use-human-brain-cells</link><description>Cortical Labs 正在建设两个数据中心，用于容纳其神经元填充芯片。该技术仍处于发展的早期阶段&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/start-up-is-building-the-first-data-centre-to-use-human-brain-cells.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 23:32:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/start-up-is-building-the-first-data-centre-to-use-human-brain-cells</guid></item><item><title>大多数大脑都会随着年龄的增长而减慢——但并非全部。科学家们刚刚了解到为什么“超级老人”保持敏锐</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/most-brains-slow-down-with-age-but-not-all-scientists-just-learned-why-superagers-stay-sharp</link><description>对具有惊人认知能力的八十多岁老人的大脑进行研究表明，如何能够在老年时保持年轻的大脑。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/most-brains-slow-down-with-age-but-not-all-scientists-just-learned-why-superagers-stay-sharp.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 23:17:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/most-brains-slow-down-with-age-but-not-all-scientists-just-learned-why-superagers-stay-sharp</guid></item><item><title>乔沙·巴赫和安德斯·桑德伯格</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/joscha-bach-anders-sandberg</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 23:02:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/joscha-bach-anders-sandberg</guid></item><item><title>太空天气可能隐藏外星信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/space-weather-could-be-hiding-alien-signals</link><description>Vishal Gajjar 博士：“如果信号因其自身恒星的环境而变宽，即使它确实存在，它也可能会滑落到我们的检测阈值以下，这可能有助于解释我们在技术签名搜索中看到的一些无线电静默。”&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/space-weather-could-be-hiding-alien-signals.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 22:47:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/space-weather-could-be-hiding-alien-signals</guid></item></channel></rss>